But thanks.

24:17.330 --> 24:19.500
You know how this is gonna go.

24:19.530 --> 24:21.970
Everyone loves Jay.

24:22.000 --> 24:26.040
They'll say you're a liar
and that it's your fault.

24:26.140 --> 24:28.140
Who are "they"?

24:28.180 --> 24:31.720
The whole town.

24:33.480 --> 24:35.180
I shouldn't have
gone behind your back.

24:40.390 --> 24:42.230
Do you have any idea
what it's like

24:42.320 --> 24:45.020
having been bad cop
for 16 years?

24:45.060 --> 24:47.860
16 years of me saying no.

24:47.900 --> 24:51.300
16 years of a daughter
who loves you and who hates...

24:58.840 --> 25:00.340
Jesus.

25:11.050 --> 25:13.650
Get back in. Get back in!

25:23.290 --> 25:23.890
If they haven't pressed charges,

25:23.990 --> 25:26.890
it means the case is weak.

25:26.990 --> 25:29.360
You're not going to jail.

25:29.460 --> 25:31.530
I guarantee that.

25:31.630 --> 25:32.660
You hear me?

25:35.830 --> 25:38.070
Why do you talk to me
as if I did it?

26:49.740 --> 26:51.380
I thought I told you
to get out of here.

26:52.610 --> 26:55.610
Just let me... This
is private property.

26:55.710 --> 26:56.740
Oh, no!

27:04.390 --> 27:06.130
Oh, what's the matter?

27:06.220 --> 27:07.960
You afraid of the cops?

27:08.060 --> 27:09.406
Maybe you should have
thought of that

27:09.430 --> 27:11.600
before you tried
to steal whatever this is.

27:11.630 --> 27:12.730
Don't.

27:15.230 --> 27:17.500
Holy...

27:41.430 --> 27:43.370
I'm not sorry.

27:43.460 --> 27:44.790
Down on the ground!

28:03.180 --> 28:05.380
What are you doing?

28:05.480 --> 28:06.610
Alex is not safe here.

28:06.650 --> 28:08.220
We're staying at my sister's.

28:10.990 --> 28:13.360
What if she needs help?

28:13.460 --> 28:15.500
I'll find a therapist
in St. Vincent,

28:15.530 --> 28:17.570
and Dr. Sing phoned in
a prescription for Valium.

28:17.660 --> 28:19.130
I'll pick it up.

28:20.830 --> 28:23.400
Okay. I'll pack some things.

28:23.500 --> 28:24.500
You're staying here.

28:28.040 --> 28:31.240
Eve, it was a party.

28:31.340 --> 28:32.910
There's no way
I could have known...

28:33.010 --> 28:35.080
But I could,
which is why I said no.

28:35.180 --> 28:37.520
How could you have known?

28:37.550 --> 28:39.690
Because I've spent
my entire life

28:39.720 --> 28:41.190
around guys like Jay.

28:44.360 --> 28:47.200
I can't be with you
right now, okay?

28:47.220 --> 28:50.590
Come up in a few days.
Then we'll talk.

28:50.700 --> 28:52.540
You should get the window fixed,

28:52.560 --> 28:54.730
and then go to the police
with the harassment.

29:06.880 --> 29:08.726
Sweetie, I thought we agreed
you'd stop looking

29:08.750 --> 29:11.090
for conspiracy theories
on the Internet.

29:11.180 --> 29:13.950
You know Dr. Kleerick
says it's not good for you.

29:14.050 --> 29:15.350
This is not the Internet.

29:15.390 --> 29:16.760
It's the "Bridgeville Post."

29:16.850 --> 29:18.120
I'm fine.

29:18.220 --> 29:20.260
Huh.

29:20.360 --> 29:24.400
"Six people were found dead,
presumably killed by a bear."

29:26.060 --> 29:29.400
"Other animals came down
the mountain in large numbers,

29:29.430 --> 29:32.770
including moose
and deer and foxes."

29:32.870 --> 29:34.310
No frogs, though.

29:34.410 --> 29:37.580
"Some locals fear
it's a black spring.

29:37.610 --> 29:41.480
"The legend of nature
turning sour is evidenced

29:41.580 --> 29:45.720
by the frozen lake being black
like a rotten tooth."

29:45.750 --> 29:50.620
Well, the "Bridgeville Post"
sure ain't what it used to be.

30:03.400 --> 30:05.240
What do you want?

30:05.270 --> 30:07.010
Maybe I should speak
to Officer Pundik.

30:08.570 --> 30:10.370
Pundik is picking up Adrian
for questioning.

30:11.580 --> 30:12.650
Why?

30:12.740 --> 30:13.470
Because he's a witness.

30:13.580 --> 30:15.350
Why do you think?

30:15.450 --> 30:17.120
Now, you can either talk to me,

30:17.150 --> 30:20.450
or you can wait an hour or two
until Pundik's done.

30:32.160 --> 30:33.930
You stay right where you are.

31:00.540 --> 31:02.286
I'm sorry.
I know this isn't what you want,

31:02.310 --> 31:05.250
but it's for the best,
the way things are right now.

31:05.310 --> 31:07.810
You understand that, don't you?

31:11.890 --> 31:15.160
Everything I do,
I do to protect you.

31:15.220 --> 31:17.160
Protect me?

31:17.220 --> 31:18.220
You're not protecting me.

31:18.290 --> 31:20.130
You're controlling me.

31:20.160 --> 31:21.830
Sweetie, I just...

31:21.900 --> 31:25.240
Please. You just don't
want me to do what you did.

31:25.300 --> 31:27.380
But guess what. I won't,
'cause I'm nothing like you.

31:30.470 --> 31:32.910
What do you mean do what I did?

31:32.970 --> 31:34.410
What do you mean?

31:34.470 --> 31:37.240
You said it yourself.
It's a small town.

31:37.310 --> 31:39.250
I know.

31:39.310 --> 31:41.150
Everyone knows.

31:42.650 --> 31:44.020
Knows what?

31:44.080 --> 31:45.110
That you were a slut.

32:05.940 --> 32:07.540
I'm gonna go pick up the Valium.

32:07.610 --> 32:09.980
Do you want to come,
or do you want to wait here?

32:28.560 --> 32:30.860
Looks amazing.

32:30.900 --> 32:32.870
It's moving against the wind.

32:37.240 --> 32:38.580
Hey, Alex.

32:38.640 --> 32:40.240
Dad, won't you
please come with us?

32:40.310 --> 32:41.680
I don't want to go with Mom.

32:41.740 --> 32:43.580
I'll be there soon, honey.

32:43.640 --> 32:45.410
You'll be fine. Where's Mom?

32:45.480 --> 32:46.810
We're at the mall.

32:46.880 --> 32:48.250
Dad, please,
I don't want to leave.

32:48.320 --> 32:50.220
It'll be fine, honey.

32:50.250 --> 32:53.050
Okay... Hello?

32:53.090 --> 32:54.230
Wow.
Alex?

32:57.590 --> 32:58.760
Signal's gone.

32:59.930 --> 33:02.200
Well, let's go back inside.

33:02.260 --> 33:04.030
It'll blow over in a minute.

33:04.100 --> 33:06.270
Nah, just... just wait.
Just wait.

33:06.330 --> 33:08.230
I want to get
a photo for the missus.

33:08.270 --> 33:10.570
Great. You do that, Pundik.
We'll see you inside.

33:10.600 --> 33:12.100
Ah, God.

33:37.130 --> 33:38.530
God.

33:38.600 --> 33:39.900
Ah!

33:41.870 --> 33:42.800
God! Get off me!

33:42.870 --> 33:44.870
Ahh!

33:49.040 --> 33:50.240
Get off me!

33:55.650 --> 33:57.390
Shit! Get off me!

34:11.670 --> 34:13.510
Get... Get in the car.
We gotta go.

34:13.570 --> 34:14.976
- What is it?
- We gotta get out of here.

34:15.000 --> 34:16.270
- Let's go.
- What's going on?

34:16.340 --> 34:17.679
- Come on! Let's go!
- Adrian.

34:17.739 --> 34:19.110
Wait in the car.

34:19.170 --> 34:20.510
Kevin!

34:32.520 --> 34:33.989
Wow.

34:34.020 --> 34:36.620
Should we wait till it's gone?

34:36.690 --> 34:38.690
It's beautiful.

34:39.860 --> 34:41.530
We'll drag the bikes.

34:41.600 --> 34:42.699
- Mm.
- This way.

34:44.530 --> 34:47.370
It's like that time
at the inn up by Chocolate Lake.

34:47.429 --> 34:49.830
Except we stayed in bed.

34:51.340 --> 34:54.380
What... This...
This way, I think.

34:54.440 --> 34:57.210
Oh, no, wrong. Wrong.

34:57.280 --> 34:58.780
Wrong direction.

34:58.850 --> 35:01.320
These trees were by the church,

35:01.380 --> 35:03.550
so that means the bikes
must be that way.

35:09.360 --> 35:11.560
It's too thick, hon.

35:11.630 --> 35:12.970
Let's get back inside.

35:13.030 --> 35:14.570
Oh!

35:14.630 --> 35:16.170
Let's go.

35:17.460 --> 35:18.730
Are you real?

35:18.800 --> 35:20.030
We are. We are. We are real.

35:21.200 --> 35:22.640
But it's all real.

35:22.700 --> 35:23.700
Put down the gun.

35:28.140 --> 35:29.540
I'm sorry.

35:29.580 --> 35:31.020
I couldn't know.

35:32.410 --> 35:33.410
Forgive me.

36:07.640 --> 36:10.140
Mrs. Raven?

36:10.180 --> 36:11.550
Are you okay?

36:14.480 --> 36:15.480
Oh...

36:25.390 --> 36:26.760
- What's going on?
- It's okay.

36:26.860 --> 36:28.660
We just need...
Help!

36:28.690 --> 36:29.690
Help!

36:30.730 --> 36:31.760
In here.

36:31.860 --> 36:34.000
Help!

36:34.030 --> 36:36.270
Over here, man. Help.

36:36.370 --> 36:37.910
Hey, get us the...
Outta here, man.

36:38.000 --> 36:39.400
- Look...
- You gotta get us out.

36:39.500 --> 36:40.846
- Calm down. Calm down.
- You don't understand.

36:40.870 --> 36:42.670
We'll die if we stay.

36:42.710 --> 36:44.486
There's something in the mist,
and then it killed my dog.

36:44.510 --> 36:45.850
You can't let us stay.

36:45.880 --> 36:47.880
Shut the... up!

36:47.910 --> 36:49.710
What has happened out there?

36:50.920 --> 36:52.760
I don't know.

36:52.850 --> 36:55.120
What are you gonna do?

36:55.220 --> 36:56.620
Find my wife and daughter.

36:56.720 --> 36:59.060
No,
what are you gonna do with us?

36:59.090 --> 37:01.090
Look, what...
Whatever's happened,

37:01.190 --> 37:02.930
I'm sure it'll be over soon.

37:03.030 --> 37:04.536
Please, I'm just here because
the Sheriff thought I was crazy

37:04.560 --> 37:06.430
when I warned them
about the mist.

37:06.530 --> 37:08.570
Don't let her out.
She looks unstable.

37:08.600 --> 37:09.700
Like she did something bad.

37:09.730 --> 37:11.970
Not to anyone good.

37:14.910 --> 37:19.550
Unlike me, you're a nice guy,

37:19.580 --> 37:21.750
and you're never gonna be
able to live with yourself

37:21.780 --> 37:24.450
if you leave us behind,
'cause, if you do, we die,

37:24.550 --> 37:25.950
and you know it.

37:26.050 --> 37:29.290
Besides, if there's
something out there,

37:29.390 --> 37:30.830
how are you gonna survive

37:30.920 --> 37:34.390
taking care of a scared
little freak on your own?

37:35.430 --> 37:39.300
Get us out, and we'll help you.

37:41.570 --> 37:43.110
The more the better.

37:46.270 --> 37:47.640
I'll find the keys.

38:21.770 --> 38:23.370
Eve Copeland?

38:24.480 --> 38:25.950
Here you go.

38:28.950 --> 38:30.390
Mrs. Carmody.

38:30.480 --> 38:32.020
You should be
ashamed of yourself.

38:32.120 --> 38:35.390
Talking to those kids about sex.
Why.

38:35.490 --> 38:37.960
Because you can raise
your child any way you want to...

38:37.990 --> 38:40.860
And clearly you have...
But leave my child out of it.

38:41.990 --> 38:43.960
You pathetic bitch.

39:35.550 --> 39:38.850
What is it?
Ever seen this before?

39:41.720 --> 39:44.460
It looks so dense.
MANâ™ª2 It's just fog.

40:08.910 --> 40:10.380
Alex?

40:10.420 --> 40:11.390
Alex?

40:11.420 --> 40:13.320
Mom?! Mom.

40:13.420 --> 40:15.160
What's going on?

40:15.250 --> 40:17.390
We need to get inside now.

40:27.970 --> 40:30.470
It's okay. We're inside.

40:30.570 --> 40:31.946
No! Don't!
There's something out there.

40:31.970 --> 40:33.770
- What?
- I don't know, but...

40:33.810 --> 40:36.780
I'm so fed up with you people
and your need for attention.

40:36.810 --> 40:38.250
It's true.

40:38.280 --> 40:40.040
Said the girl
who lied about getting raped.

40:40.950 --> 40:42.180
Come.

41:01.130 --> 41:02.530
Jesus!

41:02.630 --> 41:04.830
What's going on?

41:26.860 --> 41:28.730
Call 911!

41:35.300 --> 41:36.300
You're not getting one.

41:39.370 --> 41:41.140
Are you... kidding me?

41:42.540 --> 41:44.310
That's the way it's gonna be.

41:51.680 --> 41:52.920
All right, this way.

41:53.020 --> 41:55.360
Connor will be waiting
right outside.

42:26.180 --> 42:27.380
Did anyone call the police?

42:27.420 --> 42:29.060
No.

42:29.090 --> 42:30.460
There's no phone signal.

42:30.560 --> 42:33.030
Hey, I just want to go home.

42:33.060 --> 42:35.300
I know,
but we're gonna have to wait

42:35.390 --> 42:36.730
till we find out
what's going on.

42:37.760 --> 42:39.560
Do you trust me now?

42:41.600 --> 42:43.570
It'll be fine.

42:44.940 --> 42:46.780
The police will help us.

42:46.870 --> 42:48.810
Dad'll get here.

42:48.910 --> 42:49.910
I'm here.

42:51.580 --> 42:52.820
We're safe.

42:54.080 --> 42:57.250
I trust you.

42:59.620 --> 43:03.220
You're safe.

